import pandas as pd
Following data file is same file that I use in crouse project part1 assignment. Part1 notebook was large in size; therefore, I decided to use new notebook for part2. In addition, I have so many missing values in the dataset because few players only played in one format. For example, some players only played First-class cricket, so for those players other format entry is NaN. Therefore, I will replace other format data with zero that means the same that they did not play that format (recommended by TA)

Confusion Matrix using Seaborn Heatmap¶

In [61]:
def confusion_matrix_with_sns( actual, predicted ): 
    confusion_mat = confusion_matrix(actual,predicted)
    ax = sns.heatmap(confusion_mat, annot=True,fmt='.0f',xticklabels = ["Not Play", "Play"] ,yticklabels = ["Not Play", "Play"] )
    bottom, top = ax.get_ylim()
    ax.set_ylim(bottom +0.5 , top -0.5)
    return ax

Roc_Auc plot¶

In [62]:
def roc_auc_plot( actual, predicted ):
     fpr,  tpr, thresholds = metrics.roc_curve( actual, predicted, drop_intermediate = False )
     auc_score = metrics.roc_auc_score( actual, predicted )
     plt.plot( fpr, tpr, label='ROC curve (Area = %0.2f)' % auc_score )
     plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
     plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])
     plt.ylim([0.0, 1.05])
     plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate or [1 - True Negative Rate(Specificity)]')
     plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate(Sensitivity)')
     plt.legend(loc="lower right")
     return fpr, tpr, thresholds

Sensitivity and Specificity¶

In [63]:
def evaluate_threshold(threshold):
    print('Sensitivity:', true_positive_rate[thresholds > threshold][-1])
    print('Specificity:', 1 - false_positive_rate[thresholds > threshold][-1])
